{"key":"processedPost-7643559","value":{"id":7643559,"first":7642179,"last":7646425,"when":1195233404,"utime":"11/16/07 07:16 PM","content":"Fine verm works far better than course for the filter, and for that matter, it works better for the brf mix as well.<br /><br />NEVER use the oven tek.  It's totally bogus and ruins more crops than any other.  If I could remove that bogus tek, I would.  The convection caused by the hot oven creates airflow and turbulence that makes it the worst possible place to inoculate in.  Build a still-air glovebox, or work in a plastic trash bag or something that will contain drafts.<br /><br />If you PC your 1/2 pint jars, 45 minutes is probably enough.  Pints should be PC'd for an hour, and if steaming, they need to go for 90 to 120 minutes <i>after</i> the steam begins to escape from the lid of the pot.<br />RR","title":"Re: mixture of green and white crap","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}